-- Taiwan Stock Movers: Long Bon International, Tung Ho Steel
-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 2011-12-30T05:50:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-30/taiwan-stock-movers-eva-airways-chang-hwa-mega-financial.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual (TWSE)  moves in  Taiwan trading. (TWSE)  Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index was little changed at 7,072.08. The gauge
slid 21 percent this year, the biggest annual drop since 2008.  Long Bon International Co. (2514)  (2514 TT), a provider of
insurance products, advanced 1 percent to NT$10.65, halting a
three-day retreat. The company plans to sell NT$600 million
($19.8 million) of five-year unsecured convertible bonds,
according to a statement to the stock exchange.  Tung Ho Steel Enterprise Corp. (2006)  (2006 TT) dropped 1.1
percent to NT$26.60, the steepest loss since Dec. 19. The
steelmaker was cut to “neutral” from “buy” at Jih Sun
Securities by equity analyst Rita Hsueh.  To contact the reporter on this story:
